Linko — UI Layout Proposal

**Overview**
Linko is an inventory/supplier management web app. All four pages share a common shell (top navbar) and differ mainly in the content panel below it. This doc breaks each page into regions and suggests a React component structure so engineering can start scaffolding directly from it.

Shared visual language
- App name/logo ***"Linko"*** top-left, on a dark/gray header bar.
- A horizontal nav group (`something / menu / stuff` placeholders — to be replaced with real labels, e.g. *Dashboard / Inventory / Suppliers*).
- A row of circular avatar/icon buttons on the right (profile, notifications/bell, etc.).
- Light gray panels for cards/placeholders; mid-gray blocks for image placeholders which should map to actual product/supplier imagery later.

